metadata.name: Cape May Lighthouse
metadata.description:
Cape May, New Jersey is one of my favorite Summer haunts.  I vacation there most summers.  One of my favorite things to do is climb the Cape May Lighthouse.  The light has 199 steps and was built in 1859.  It is an active lighthouse that still guides ships from the Atlantic to the Delaware Bay.  This evening, the sunset popped and created a beautiful sky and reflection!

Photographer: Jason Betzner

Year Created: 2021

Location: Cape May, New Jersey

Camera: Canon EOS 6D

Aperture: F/9

ISO: 100

Exposure time: 1/125s

Focal Length: 70mm
